title: Vantage Health Plan/Team Colvin 20K ITT and Criter
2014 CHILLY ROGER METRIC CENTURY
description: Join us for the 15th Annual Chilly Roger 2014 Bicycle Tour and Jolly Roger Cycling Club’s (JRC),  membership drive. The first 120 registered riders will receive a T-shirt. Enjoy SWLA’s best routes each fully stocked with breakpoints.
course: The routes range from 10-62.5 miles. Each route consist of smooth, flat surface.  The lead bicycle riders with have a police escort.
registration: $35 online registation  $45 off line at the starting point.  $20 for Jolly Roger Cycling club members
notes: After the chili ride, indulge in a hot bowl of chili and vote for your favorite chili chef.  Stick around for a chance to win a Yeti Cooler or one of many other door prizes.  You may also choose to join the Jolly Roger Cycling Club, (JRC).  Members promote cycling in our area and use funds to sponsor cycling.  This past year members sponsored KPLC’s Community Christmas by purchasing 15 bicycles and helmets for needy families.
directions: WW Lewis Middle School, 1752 Cypress St. Sulphur, LA From I-10, Exit 21  head North on LA 27 West on to Cypress

title: GULF COAST REGIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP
description:
This is the Gulf Coast Regional Championship Race
We are putting the best of Louisiana against the best from Mississippi.
Lets get it on
course: Rolling terrain, similar to the trails in Brookhaven, Ms or the trails in Ridgeland for those who haven't ridden the course.
registration: We encourage everyone to register for this event online at USA Cycling.  This will assist the race preparation, as well as shorten your time to pick up your packet on race day.
notes: This race is an invitational only event for riders who finished in the top 10 overall in either the LMBCS, or MORCS.  If you did not, achieve this, then you would need to contact the series directors for that series to gain an entry.
directions: The address for the race is 211 Parish Park Rd, Ruston, LA 71270.
